#!/bin/bash

cat << 'EOF'
Multi-Agent Development Workflow
================================

A workflow for coordinating multiple Claude agents working on isolated
git worktrees, with code review via git-appraise before merging.

WORKSPACE STRUCTURE
-------------------

  origin/main (GitHub)
      │
      │ (final PR when feature complete)
      │
  ~/workspaces/<feature>/
      │
      ├── <repo-name>/            ← Coordinator workspace (you + claude)
      │   └── .git/agent-data/    ← Agent status tracking
      │
      ├── <agent-name>/           ← Agent 1 worktree (tmux tab)
      ├── <agent-name>/           ← Agent 2 worktree (tmux tab)
      └── <agent-name>/           ← Agent 3 worktree (tmux tab)

COMMANDS
--------

  agent-workspace <feature>
  agent-workspace <repo> <feature>
      Initialize an agent workspace.
      - Single arg: use current directory as workspace
      - Two args: clone repo to ~/workspaces/<feature>/<repo-name>/
      - Creates <username>/<feature> branch
      - Starts tmux session with coordinator claude

  agent-spawn <task-description> [agent-name]
      Spawn an agent in a new tmux tab.
      - agent-name: short name for branch/tab (auto-generated if not provided)
      - Creates git worktree at ~/workspaces/<feature>/<agent-name>/
      - Opens new tmux window with claude working on task
      - Agent has restricted file access (only their worktree)

  agent-list [json]
      List all agents spawned from this workspace.
      - Shows window name, branch, worktree directory, status
      - Use 'json' argument for machine-readable output

  agent-cleanup <agent-name>
      Remove an agent after merge.
      - Kills tmux window
      - Removes git worktree
      - Deletes agent branch
      - Cleans up agent data

  agent-help
      Show this help message.

AGENT LIFECYCLE
---------------

  1. agent-spawn "task" starts agent with task
  2. Agent works in isolated worktree
  3. Agent runs: submit-review "description"
  4. Agent exits with /exit (waits for feedback)
  5. Status becomes "review_requested"
  6. User reviews in vim (<leader>rr)
  7. On reject (<leader>rx): agent auto-restarts with feedback
  8. On accept (<leader>ra): branch is merged
  9. agent-cleanup removes the agent

VIM KEYBINDINGS
---------------

  Review workflow (recommended):
    <leader>rr    List agents waiting for review, cd to selected agent's worktree
    <leader>ra    Accept: merge branch, return to main workspace
    <leader>rx    Reject: write feedback, restart agent, return to main
    <leader>rq    Quit review without decision, return to main

  File exploration (while in agent worktree):
    <leader>ri    FZF changed files (opens with inline gutter diff)
    <leader>rs    Side-by-side vimdiff of current file
    <leader>ro    Close side-by-side diff

  Comments:
    <leader>rc    Comment on line with context
    <leader>rC    Comment without context (diff-aware)

  Legacy (git checkout workflow):
    <leader>rp    FZF list PRs via git-appraise
    <leader>rl    List pending reviews (text)

TYPICAL SESSION
---------------

  # 1. Start feature workspace
  cd ~/repos/myproject
  agent-workspace new-feature

  # Or clone to ~/workspaces/
  agent-workspace ~/repos/myproject new-feature

  # 2. Spawn agents for subtasks
  agent-spawn "implement user authentication"
  agent-spawn "add API endpoints for users"
  agent-spawn "write unit tests for auth module"

  # 3. Monitor agents
  agent-list

  # 4. When agent submits (bell notification), review in vim
  <leader>rr           # Select agent, cd to their worktree
  # Browse code with LSP, run tests, etc.
  <leader>rc           # Add comments if needed

  # 5. Accept or reject
  <leader>ra           # Accept: merges and returns to main
  # or
  <leader>rx           # Reject: restarts agent with feedback

  # 6. Cleanup after merge
  agent-cleanup <agent-name>

  # 7. Final PR to upstream when feature complete
  git push upstream <username>/new-feature
  gh pr create

AGENT STATUS FILES
------------------

  Located in .git/agent-data/<agent-name>/:
    status       - working | review_requested | changes_requested | approved | merged
    task         - Original task description
    system-prompt - Agent's system instructions
    pr-info.json - Branch, target, commit, description (after submit)
    feedback.md  - Reviewer feedback (after rejection)
    launch.sh    - Script to start agent initially

RESUMING AGENTS
---------------

  agent-continue <agent-name> "prompt"
      Resume an agent with feedback (used by vim on reject).
      Can also be run manually from the main workspace.

EOF
